German Air Controllers Will Bid for Spanish Business, FTD Says

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-05-09T06:51:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/german-air-controllers-will-bid-for-spanish-business-ftd-says.html
German air-traffic control authorities
are seeking to bid for partial control of Spanish air space,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing the head of
 Germany ’s DFS agency.  Deutsche Flugsicherung GmbH, the state-owned air-traffic
control agency will submit a formal offer to Spanish authorities
to control parts of the southern European countries’ air
traffic, the newspaper said in today’s edition, citing Dieter Kaden, the agency’s chief.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer in Dusseldorf, Germany via 
 acremer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
